<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<CONTENT id="_3793111_1"><TITLE value="Submission and Documentation Instructions"/><TITLECOLOR
  value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;div&gt;You are required to submit all of your documented evidence for the below work,&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;each of the submissions must contain the following or they will be rejected&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;ol style="list-style-type: decimal;"&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Activities&lt;/strong&gt;:&#xd;
&lt;ol style="list-style-type: decimal;"&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Evidence that you completed each part of the activity, these should be signed screen shots (one option would be the snip tool in Windows)&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Packet Tracer Activities&lt;/strong&gt;:&#xd;
&lt;ol style="list-style-type: decimal;"&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;The completed Packet Tracer file&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;The completed documentation that accompanies the Packet Tracer file including (open the PDF files in Microsoft Word to edit):&#xd;
&lt;ol style="list-style-type: decimal;"&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Screen shots of you completing the tasks&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Answers to any questions in the document&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Any other evidence that you feel will help you prove you completed the work&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lab Activities&lt;/strong&gt;:&#xd;
&lt;ol style="list-style-type: decimal;"&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;A .txt file for each config of each device (for example if your exercise has 2 routers and a switch you should include 3 files called R1.txt, R2.txt and S1.txt with the copy and pasted running-configuration of the devices in each)&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Completed lab documentation including:&lt;br&gt;&#xd;
&lt;ol style="list-style-type: decimal;"&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Screen shots to demonstrate you completed steps in the labs&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Answers to any questions in the document&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Any other evidence you feel will help you prove you completed the work&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#xd;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All documentation&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/div&gt;&#xd;
&lt;ol style="list-style-type: decimal;"&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Screen shots of you entering every command required by the document (for example: if the document asks you to configure a router network interface, you must show screen shots to verify you did).&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Screen shots to verify your commands&amp;nbsp;are correctly configured. This means if you are configuring networks or routing you must&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;demonstrate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;that they work, this should be done through testing (ping,&amp;nbsp;debug&amp;nbsp;or&amp;nbsp;show&amp;nbsp;commands will be useful here (most labs will ask you to verify instructions anyway)).&lt;/li&gt;&#xd;
&lt;li style="list-style-type: inherit;"&gt;Where appropriate, sign your screenshots, or add a "whoami" insert. Example here:&lt;br&gt;&lt;img style="height: auto;" src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-30139864_1" alt="" width="223" height="131"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span bb:beforeshowfunc="" bb:overwritenavitems="" bb:menuorder="openId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,open_with_browser_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,open_with_bbdrive_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,openWebId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,view360Id_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,*separator*,*separator*,ax-ally-placeholder_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,ax-ally-markForAxAnalysis_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,*separator*,*separator*,content_settings_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,content_editSettings_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,content_edit_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,properties_folder_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,itemcarot_managerecord_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,comments_tool_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,subscriptions_list_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,content_readfile_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,content_overwrite_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,passes_tool_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,permissions_tool_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,content_add_alignment_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,content_tracking_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,content_versions_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,*separator*,*separator*,bookmarkId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,itemsId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,packagesId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,emailId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,removeContentFolderId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,*separator*,copyContentId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,moveContentId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,*separator*,removeContentId_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,*separator*,Metadata_General_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,Metadata_Dublin_Core_06ed26c2fb8c4962980422777b896407,Metadata_IMS_06ed26c2fb8c49629